record.dcterms:title: 1979 Faculty Show
record.dcterms:description: Faculty members performing in the skit "History of Art 609B: Fellini's 'Beast of the Gods' in the History of Western Thought: An Ontological, Phenomenological and Tautological Approach" as part of the 1979 Faculty Show "Curriculi, Curricula!" Pictured: back row (left to right) Gerard Defaux (satyr), Greg Dickerson (Silenus), Neil Forsyth (satyr), Kathleen Slane Wright (nymph), Barbara Lane (nymph), Machteld Mellink (nymph). Front row (Left to Right) Kirsty Dickerson (young Bacchus), Richard Ellis (Mercury), Matthew Yarczower (Jupiter), Dale Kinney (Cybele), Kenneth Strothkamp (Poseidon), Jean Potter (Ceres), Charles Mitchell (Apollo). Backdrop designed by Fritz Janschka. From the James Snyder files.

record.dcterms:title: Students in large dorm room
record.dcterms:description: Students are in very large dorm room, with a door to the left and a door to the right. Three students are playing cards and drinking milk, one students is sewing basketballs, another student is playing the accordian, and one last student is playing the drums. There are photos on a small stand, as well as a large area rug, additional cushions on a window bench, a rocking chair, a desk, and a wicker waste basket. There is electricity in the room, as there are cords from the lamps.
